  "prompt": "Which are the top 5 Bollywood songs of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, several Bollywood songs became very popular and received widespread acclaim. Here are five of the most notable ones:\n\n1. **\"Gerua\"** from *Dilwale* - Sung by Arijit Singh and Antara Mitra, this romantic track featuring Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol became a massive hit.\n\n2. **\"Matargashti\"** from *Tamasha* - Composed by A.R. Rahman and sung by Mohit Chauhan, this lively and playful song starred Ranbir Kapoor and Deepika Padukone.\n\n3. **\"Prem Ratan Dhan Payo\"** from *Prem Ratan Dhan Payo* - The title track of this Salman Khan-starrer became hugely popular, with music by Himesh Reshammiya and vocals by Palak Muchhal.\n\n4. **\"Sooraj Dooba Hain\"** from *Roy* - This energetic party anthem was sung by Arijit Singh and Aditi Singh Sharma, with music by Amaal Mallik.\n\n5. **\"Chittiyaan Kalaiyaan\"** from *Roy* - Another hit from the movie *Roy*, this song was sung by Kanika Kapoor and became extremely popular for its catchy tune.\n\nThese songs not only topped music charts but also became favorites at various events and parties throughout the year.",
